ou want to make your own specification, you're welcome to. I can't force you to follow the spec I have designed, but I hope that you will.<br /><br />Like you said, it's an issue that sd2snes is using 44308hz. Yes, I was wrong in my initial assessment that this was a minor difference. It's bigger than I thought when I did the math on it. But it's an example of why we all need to do the same thing. We can't have each author doing their own thing, or the software won't be compatible.

		

