 be good to &quot;agree on an official sample rate&quot;. I hope you are no longer feeling offended by that sentence.<br />For the at <strong>least three</strong> volume changes: you have changed your definition at least once some years ago, and twice in this thread. Maybe it was unfair to count the latter two as &quot;changes to the specification&quot;. From my point of view, when trying to figure the initial volume setting: it did really seem as if the volume were changing day by day (first I stumbled through your three conflicting definitions, and then I ran into the conflicting akira and sd2snes implementions). There is definitely some sort of a mess, and it was really hard to figure out what is going on with that register.<br /><strong>appears to be better to set volume=FFh for compatibility</strong> - that was meant to be a constructive suggestion for maintaining backwards compatibility &amp; compatibility with sd2snes, and I was really thinking that it would be a good and simple solution without any negative side effects (at that time I wasn't aware about that Skrillex demo).<br /><strong>I am considering to support both .pcm and .wav</strong> - that was annoying you?

		

