		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />&lt;tepples&gt; To placate the Warner Bros., I'd almost be more willing to just have your MSU test suite play a &quot;You fail it!&quot; wave.<br /><br />Not nearly annoying enough :P<br /><br />&lt;tepples&gt; It's already trivial to include ogg123 and a batch file with your download.<br /><br />Less trivial to include ogg123.exe, ogg123.app, ogg123.linux, ogg123.linux64, ogg123.bsd, ogg123.bsd64, ogg123.solaris, ogg123.haiku, etc.<br /><br />But yeah, ogg123.exe will cover 95% of users. If we have a standard, then we can let people include the Windows one with the download, and a link to a webpage hosting all the other versions.<br /><br />&lt;tepples&gt; Is Power Slide FX's problem the same as Mario Adventure's?<br /><br />I don't know anything about Mario Adventure. Power Slide FX relied on uninitialized memory and had no test signature to ensure the SRAM contents were still initialized.

		

